## 1. Modeling Goal

The primary modeling goal is to predict **FinalGrade**, a numeric measure of student academic performance. This is the technical outcome used for the regression modeling workflow. In the broader retention context, predicted final grade can be translated into academic-risk segments that support proactive advising, tutoring, financial aid review, attendance follow-up, and engagement interventions.

Enrollment status is retained as a predictor and context variable rather than modeled as the outcome. This keeps the modeling task focused on academic performance while still connecting the results to student retention and student-success decision-making.

