## 3. Data Split and Reproducibility

The data is split into an 80% training set and a 20% testing set. The training set is used for model fitting and cross-validation. The testing set is held out until final evaluation to estimate how well each model generalizes to unseen student records.

The same random seed is used throughout the modeling workflow so that results can be reproduced.

