## 13. PCA Discussion

Principal Component Analysis could make sense if the main goal were to reduce redundancy among correlated predictors, especially the grade components and teacher evaluation items. In this dataset, there are multiple academic performance variables and many teacher evaluation questions. Combining related variables into components could reduce dimensionality and improve stability for some models.

For this portfolio report, I use a simpler engineered feature, **CumulativeTeacherEval**, to summarize the 16 teacher evaluation items. This keeps the model easier to explain. I would consider PCA more strongly if the project were focused on maximizing prediction accuracy with less concern for interpretability.

```{r pca-discussion-table}
pca_discussion <- tibble::tribble(
  ~Question, ~Answer,
  "Does PCA make sense for this dataset?", "Yes, potentially. The teacher evaluation items and grade-related variables may contain correlated information.",
