## 14. Cluster Analysis Discussion

Cluster analysis could also make sense for this dataset if the goal were to identify student profiles before supervised modeling. For example, students might cluster into groups such as high-performing/high-engagement, low-attendance/high-risk, financially pressured, or high-support-service usage. Those cluster labels could then be used as additional predictors in the supervised models.

For this project, I keep the main workflow supervised and focused on predicting **FinalGrade**. However, cluster analysis would be a strong future enhancement for intervention design because different risk groups may require different types of support.

```{r cluster-discussion-table}
cluster_discussion <- tibble::tribble(
  ~Question, ~Answer,
  "Does cluster analysis make sense for this dataset?", "Yes. Student records include academic, attendance, financial, support-service, and engagement variables that could reveal meaningful student profiles.",
